    "connections": [
      {
        "from": "Sofia",
        "to": "Rila Monastery",
        "method": "Direct bus from Sofia Central Bus Station to Rila Monastery, usually the easiest day-trip option in season (about 2h 20m-2h 30m each way)",
        "cost": "₹690–₹1,150"
      },
      {
        "from": "Rila Monastery",
        "to": "Plovdiv",
        "method": "Return to Sofia, then take a BDZ fast train from Sofia Central Railway Station to Plovdiv (about 2h 40m-3h 10m total rail time after you get back to the capital)",
        "cost": "₹460–₹690"
      },
      {
        "from": "Plovdiv",
        "to": "Veliko Tarnovo",
        "method": "Union Ivkoni or Biomet coach, sometimes with a transfer, is usually simpler than stitching together BDZ regional trains on this corridor (about 4h-5h)",
        "cost": "₹690–₹1,150"
      },
      {
        "from": "Veliko Tarnovo",
        "to": "Bansko",
        "method": "Take a Union Ivkoni or Biomet bus via Sofia; there is no clean direct rail option, so buses are the most practical public-transport choice (about 7h-9h total)",
        "cost": "₹1,380–₹1,840"
      },
      {
        "from": "Bansko",
        "to": "Sozopol",
        "method": "Bus back via Sofia or Plovdiv and continue on a long-distance Union Ivkoni/Biomet service to Burgas, then finish with the local bus to Sozopol (usually 10h+ total)",
        "cost": "₹1,840–₹2,760"
      }
    ],
    "extras": [
      "Use BDZ where it clearly saves stress, especially Sofia-Plovdiv, but do not force rail everywhere: several Bulgaria cross-country links are easier by Union Ivkoni or Biomet coach.",
      "Rila Monastery itself is free, but carry small cash for the museum, tower ticket, bakery snacks and bus station kiosks because card acceptance is patchy away from Sofia.",
      "For Bansko, think in two seasons: December-March for skiing and snow; May-September for hiking, mehanas and quieter mountain scenery.",
      "Sozopol is most enjoyable in June or September if you want warm sea weather without the full July-August weekend crowd from Burgas and Sofia.",
      "Vegetarian travelers do well with shopska salad, grilled vegetables, banitsa, bean soups and sirene dishes, all easy to find from Sofia to the coast."
    ],
